Since the widths of PBGs formed with (MgF2/MoO3)N 1D-PC are pretty significant, it can lead to a serious deterioration in the transparency of ST-OSCs, if careful λB is not selected. Even when λB is selected in the middle of the visible region, the structure becomes completely opaque. Thus, only the low wavelength tail of the PBG can be used when the aim is to modify the transmittance of the ST-OSC while reducing the dominance of the x¯λ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
