AVTs should be taken as a basis as well as color coordinates for STs. In ST-OSC/(MgF2/MoO3)N, the changes of AVT, Δu,v and CCT obtained for different λBs according to the period values of PBG of 1D-PC are shown in Fig. 4a–c respectively. The AVT of ST-OSC decreases from 38.52% to 20% as a result of 1D-PC integration. In particular, the highest AVT for each λB is seen in structures with N = 2 periods, as expected. Because PBGs of structures with N = 2 periods have less reflectivity and reduce the transparency of the structure less than PBGs in other periods.Figure 4
